    "= 1 2A ss ′ τ τ ′ abcd q∈all k α,k β ∈mBZ V (q)λ τ,ab (k α, q)λ * τ ′,dc (k β, q) × ĉ † τ as (k α)ĉ † τ ′ cs ′ (k β + q)ĉ τ ′ ds ′ (k β)ĉ τ bs (k α + q) (25) Ĥsub = - 1 A k α ∈mBZ sτ ab     G k β ∈mBZ s ′ τ ′ cd V (G)λ * τ ′,dc (k β, G)ρ 0 τ s,dc (k β)     λ τ,ab (k α, q)ĉ † τ as (k α)ĉ τ bs (k α) + 1 A k α ∈mBZ sτ ab q∈all cd V (q)λ * τ,bc (k α, q)ρ 0 τ s,dc (k α + q)λ τ,ad (k α, q)ĉ † τ as (k α)ĉ τ bs (k α).",
    "(26)We have split Ĥint into a piece Ĥint, n.o.",
    "corresponding to the interaction normalordered with respect to the Fock vacuum, and a one-body 'subtraction' correction Ĥsub, which corresponds the term in Eq. 22 with the proper form factors and other extra degrees of freedom of TBG restored.",
    "More precisely, Ĥsub is given by the negative of the Hartree and Fock mean-field potentials (see Section 3 for an introduction to Hartree-Fock) of the state ρ 0 for the vacuum-normal-ordered interaction Ĥint, n.o..",
    "This implies that ĤBM would be the mean-field Hamiltonian in the state ρ 0 -the interpretation is that interactions are 'measured relative' to ρ 0."
